2 Garlic
1 Tomato
1 packet Filo Pastry
1 sachet Chilli Flakes
1 packet Passata
1 packet Rocket leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
2 Courgette
1 Radish
1 drizzle olive oil
30 g butter
1 drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Slice tomato and courgette into 0.5cm-thick rounds.
• Thinly slice garlic.
• In a medium bowl, combine tomato, courgette, garlic and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

• To a small microwave-safe bowl, add the butter and microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.
• Evenly stack 5 sheets of filo pastry (two separate stacks for 4 people), brushing the melted butter between each layer. Place on a lined oven tray.
• Spoon passata (see ingredients) evenly into centre of the pastry, leaving a 4cm border around the edge. Sprinkle over a pinch of chilli flakes
(if using).
• Arrange sliced courgette, tomato and garlic on top of passata. Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese. Season with salt and pepper.

• Carefully fold pastry edges over filling, leaving the centre exposed.
• Bake galette until golden, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice radish.
• In a large bowl, combine radish, baby leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Slice ratatouille filo galette. Divide galettes between plates.
• Serve with radish salad. Enjoy!